title: Photos of the week
text:
Pictures | Fri Mar 16, 2018 | 11:35am EDT Photos of the week 
Saudi men perform a stunt known as "sidewall skiing" (driving on two wheels) as a youth takes a selfie in Tabuk, Saudi Arabia, March 11. REUTERS/Mohamed Al Hwaity Reuters / Sunday, March 11, 2018 Saudi men perform a stunt known as "sidewall skiing" (driving on two wheels) as a youth takes a selfie in Tabuk, Saudi Arabia, March 11. REUTERS/Mohamed Al Hwaity Close 1 / 20 
Students participate in a march in support of the National School Walkout in Queens, New York, March 14. REUTERS/Shannon Stapleton Reuters / Wednesday, March 14, 2018 Students participate in a march in support of the National School Walkout in Queens, New York, March 14. REUTERS/Shannon Stapleton Close 2 / 20 
U.S. President Donald Trump speaks while participating in a tour of U.S.-Mexico border wall prototypes near the Otay Mesa Port of Entry in San Diego, California, March 13. REUTERS/Kevin Lamarque Close 3 / 20 
A child sleeps in a bag in the village of Beit Sawa, eastern Ghouta, Syria, March 15. REUTERS/Omar Sanadiki Reuters / Thursday, March 15, 2018 A child sleeps in a bag in the village of Beit Sawa, eastern Ghouta, Syria, March 15. REUTERS/Omar Sanadiki Close 4 / 20 
People attend a rally marking the fourth anniversary of Russia's annexation of Ukraine's Crimea region in the Black Sea port of Sevastopol, Crimea, March 14. REUTERS/Kepa Fuentes Close 6 / 20 
Druid Malachy, played by Ciaron Davies, reacts with a European eagle-owl named 'Cracker' during the re-enactment of the first landing of Saint Patrick in Ireland at Inch Abbey in Downpatrick, Northern Ireland, March 11. REUTERS/Clodagh Kilcoyne Reuters / Sunday, March 11, 2018 Druid Malachy, played by Ciaron Davies, reacts with a European eagle-owl named 'Cracker' during the re-enactment of the first landing of Saint Patrick in Ireland at Inch Abbey in Downpatrick, Northern Ireland, March 11. REUTERS/Paul Hanna Reuters / Monday, March 12, 2018 Simon Patmore of Australia lies in the snow after winning the men's snowboard cross SB-UL final event as fellow competitor Ben Tudhope of Australia rushes to congratulate him during the Pyeongchang Paralympics, March 12. Visitors are seen under blooming cherry blossoms at the East Lake Cherry Blossom Park in Wuhan, Hubei province, China, March 9. REUTERS/Stringer Reuters / Friday, March 09, 2018 Visitors are seen under blooming cherry blossoms at the East Lake Cherry Blossom Park in Wuhan, Hubei province, China, March 9. REUTERS/Stringer Close 9 / 20
